The paper deals with a data structure for representing sequences of symbols and supporting various operations on them. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses compression techniques, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) or databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
